h2. Download

There are several ways to download <span class="keyword">Aquarium</span>. Which way is right for you depends on how you want to use it.

h3. Rubygems

This is the preferred approach. Non-windows users may have to use sudo. Install or update to the latest with:

<pre>
gem install aquarium
gem update aquarium
</pre>  

or if you want an older version:

<pre>
gem install aquarium -v 0.1.0
gem update aquarium -v 0.1.0
</pre>  

h3. Direct download

Get it from "Rubyforge":http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=4281

h3. Subversion

Check it out:

<pre>
svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/aquarium/trunk aquarium_trunk
</pre>

or

<pre>
svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/aquarium/tags/{svn_tag: }/aquarium aquarium_{svn_tag: }
</pre>

See the "README":rdoc/files/README.html for details about how to build it.